'''[[大堡礁|大堡礁]]'''是世界上最大的[[珊瑚礁|珊瑚礁]]群<ref name=UNEP>{{cite web |author=UNEP World Conservation Monitoring Centre |year=1980 |title=Protected Areas and World Heritage - Great Barrier Reef World Heritage Area |url=http://sea.unep-wcmc.org/sites/wh/gbrmp.html |publisher=[[Department_of_the_Environment_and_Heritage|Department of the Environment and Heritage]] |accessdate=2006-06-10 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081013162100/http://sea.unep-wcmc.org/sites/wh/gbrmp.html |archivedate=2008-10-13 }}</ref><ref name=GBRWHV>{{cite web |author= |year= |title=Great Barrier Reef World Heritage Values |url=http://www.deh.gov.au/heritage/worldheritage/sites/gbr/values.html |accessdate=2006-11-10 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061006181457/http://www.deh.gov.au/heritage/worldheritage/sites/gbr/values.html |archivedate=2006-10-06 }}</ref>，由大约3000个礁体和900个岛屿组成，绵延2,600公里（1,616英里），覆盖约344,400平方公里<ref>{{cite web|author=Fodor's|title=Great Barrier Reef Travel Guide|url=http://www.fodors.com/miniguides/mgresults.cfm?destination=great_barrier@230&cur_section=ove|accessdate=2006-08-08|archive-date=2013-04-14|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6FsFanuZe?url=http://www.fodors.com/world/australia-and-the-pacific/australia/queensland/great-barrier-reef/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=1975review>{{cite web |author=Department of the Environment and Heritage |title=Review of the Great Barrier Reef Marine Park Act 1975 |url=http://www.deh.gov.au/coasts/publications/gbr-marine-park-act.html |accessdate=2006-11-02 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061018005108/http://www.deh.gov.au/coasts/publications/gbr-marine-park-act.html |archivedate=2006-10-18 }}</ref>。大堡礁位於[[澳大利亚|澳大利亚]]东北部[[昆士兰州|昆士兰州]]的[[珊瑚海|珊瑚海]]上，其中很大一部分是由[[大堡礁海洋公园|大堡礁海洋公园]]负责保护的。

大堡礁受到的[[环境|环境]]压力包括：来自径流的低劣水质，其中含有悬浮沉积物、过剩营养物、[[杀虫剂|杀虫剂]]，且[[盐度|盐度]]波动不定；[[气候变化|气候变化]]的影响，例如[[溫室效應|气温上升]]、[[熱帶氣旋|风暴]]天气以及[[珊瑚礁白化|珊瑚礁白化]]现象；此外[[棘冠海星|棘冠海星]]的周期性大量出现，过度捕捞导致[[食物链|食物链]]破坏，以及运输航线上的的[[石油|石油]]泄漏或不当的压载水排放都会影响大堡礁的[[生态|生态]]环境。

==水质==
[[Image:Gladstone,_Queensland,_Australia_-_Storage_Silos_on_the_Gladstone_waterfront.JPG|thumb]]
水质问题于1989年首次被列为大堡礁的威胁因素。<ref name="pressures">{{cite web |url=http://www.environment.gov.au/coasts/publications/pubs/gbr-marine-park-act-chapters-7.pdf |title=Pressures on the Marine Park |date=2006 |work=Review of the Great Barrier Reef Marine Park Act 1975 |publisher=Commonwealth of Australia |accessdate=2009-03-15 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080730020711/http://www.environment.gov.au/coasts/publications/pubs/gbr-marine-park-act-chapters-7.pdf |archivedate=2008-07-30 }}</ref>大堡礁的集水区由三个主要河流和成百上千条小溪流组成，占地面积423000平方千米（約163000平方英里）。<ref name=Henderson>{{cite journal|last=Henderson|first=Fiona|coauthors=Kroon, Frederike|date=2009|title=Overview of CSIRO Water Quality Research in the Great Barrier Reef, 2003～2008|publisher=[[CSIRO|CSIRO]]|url=http://www.csiro.au/files/files/przy.pdf|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091022010556/http://csiro.au/files/files/przy.pdf|archivedate=2009-10-22|journal=|access-date=2010-01-26}}</ref>昆士兰州沿岸有几个主要的中心城市，包括[[凯恩斯_(昆士兰州)|凯恩斯]]、[[汤斯维尔|汤斯维尔]]、[[麦凯|麦凯]]、[[罗克汉普顿|罗克汉普顿]]以及工业城市[[格拉德斯通|格拉德斯通]]。凯恩斯和汤斯维尔是其中两个最大的沿海城市，各大约拥有15万人口。<ref>{{cite web|title=Office of Economic and Statistical Research|publisher=Office of Economic and Statistical Research|url=http://www.oesr.qld.gov.au|accessdate=2006-05-28|archive-date=1999-12-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/19991216055420/http://www.oesr.qld.gov.au/|dead-url=yes}}</ref> 

影响珊瑚礁健康的主要水质变量有水温、盐浓度、营养含量，悬浮泥沙浓度<ref name=EPAQ/>和农药浓度<ref name=Henderson/>。在大堡礁区域存活的生物能够适应其水质的变化，然而一旦这种变化超过临界阈值，就会对这些生物造成不利影响。河排放物是最大的营养素的来源<ref name= waterquality/>，在热带洪水爆发时会对礁石造成极大的污染，这种污染90%来自农场。<ref name=EPAQ>{{cite web |date=2003 |url=http://www.epa.qld.gov.au/register/p01258bs.pdf |title=Coastal water quality |work=The State of the Environment Report Queensland 2003 |publisher=Environment Protection Agency Queensland |format=PDF |accessdate=2007-06-07 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070614223713/http://www.epa.qld.gov.au/register/p01258bs.pdf |archivedate=2007-06-14 }}</ref>

大堡礁附近的集水区的水被人类用于各种用途，3000座礁石中大约700座成了危险区<ref name="wwf.org.au">{{cite web|url=http://wwf.org.au/news/governments-sit-on-hands-while-pollution-damages-reef-wwf/|title=Governments sit on hands while pollution damages Reef: WWF|accessdate=2007-06-07|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070901124346/http://www.wwf.org.au/news/governments-sit-on-hands-while-pollution-damages-reef-wwf/|archivedate=2007-09-01}}</ref>。由於自然酸性物沉积和耕作化学物质的排放，以及海岸线发展和作为自然过滤器的沿海湿地流失，这些区域的水质已经严重下降。<ref name=wetlands>{{cite web |author=Great Barrier Reef Marine Park Authority |year= |title=Wetlands |url=http://www.gbrmpa.gov.au/corp_site/key_issues/water_quality/wetlands |accessdate=2007-03-13 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061002034022/http://www.gbrmpa.gov.au/corp_site/key_issues/water_quality/wetlands |archivedate=2006-10-02 }}</ref>集水区的工业包括大约262平方千米的[[棉花|棉花]]种植；合计158平方千米的340个奶牛场，平均每个占地2平方千米；288平方千米的放牧场；大约8000平方千米的[[园艺|园艺]]种植区，包括[[香蕉|香蕉]]种植、[[甘蔗|甘蔗]]种植以及谷物种植；1200平方千米的[[小麦|小麦]]种植区；6000到7000平方千米的[[大麦|大麦]]种植区以及[[高粱|高粱]]和[[玉米|玉米]]种植区。<ref name="Brodie07">{{cite web|date=2007|author=Brodie, J.|url=http://www.actfr.jcu.edu.au/Publications/ACTFRreports/06～07_NMZ%20technical%20final%20March%202007%20main.pdf|title=Nutrient management zones in the Great Barrier Reef Catchment: A decision system for zone selection|publisher=Australian Centre for Tropical Freshwater Research|format=PDF|accessdate=2007-06-07}}{{dead link|date=2017年12月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>在棉花、[[奶制品|奶制品]]、[[牛肉|牛肉]]生产，园艺业和[[制糖业|制糖业]]中使用[[肥料|肥料]]对于保证产量和收益是至关重要的。然而，化肥和甘蔗收获方式的副产品构成了大堡礁[[潟湖|潟湖]]地表径流的成分。<ref name= "Brodie07"/><ref name=Keypoints>{{cite web |author=Australian Government Productivity Commission |year=2003 |title=Industries, Land Use and Water Quality in the Great Barrier Reef Catchment - Key Points |url=http://www.pc.gov.au/study/gbr/finalreport/keypoints.html |accessdate=2006-05-29 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060906134413/http://www.pc.gov.au/study/gbr/finalreport/keypoints.html |archivedate=2006-09-06 }}</ref>潮湿[[热带地区|热带地区]]的甘蔗种植业和干燥热带地区的放牧业是首要的农业生产活动，二者都是影响水质的重要因素。<ref name=Keypoints/>在大堡礁水域中常见的工业污染物[[铜|铜]]已被证明干扰了[[珊瑚虫|珊瑚虫]]的发育<ref>{{cite web|author=Emma Young|publisher=New Scientist|date=2003-11-18|title=Copper decimates coral reef spawning|url=http://www.newscientist.com/article.ns?id=dn4391|accessdate=2006-08-26|archive-date=2008-04-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080415231053/http://www.newscientist.com/article.ns?id=dn4391|dead-url=no}}</ref>，而洪水泛滥则与水中[[氮|氮]]和[[磷|磷]]的含量升高有关<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gbrmpa.gov.au/corp_site/info_services/publications/research_publications/rp068/index.html |title=Research Publication No. 68 - Flood Plumes in the Great Barrier Reef: Spatial and Temporal Patterns in Composition and Distribution |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070829134140/http://www.gbrmpa.gov.au/corp_site/info_services/publications/research_publications/rp068/index.html |archivedate=2007-08-29 |access-date=2010-01-26 }}</ref>。据观察，在2007年2月，由於受季风气候的影响，大量的泥沙径流已经达到礁石的最外层区域。<ref>{{cite web|author=CSIRO|authorlink=CSIRO|year=2007|title=CSIRO imagery shows outer Great Barrier Reef at risk from river plumes|url=http://www.csiro.au/news/ps2t8.html|accessdate=2007-03-13|archive-date=2011-01-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110113114057/http://www.csiro.au/news/ps2t8.html|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

雨水径流对凯恩斯南部地区的影响最大，这裡的年降水量达3000毫米，而珊瑚礁距离海岸不到30公里。过度放牧、过量使用化肥与农药让农业径流受到了污染。自从澳大利亚引进了[[欧洲|欧洲]]的农耕模式，农田土壤的污染程度升高了800%，无机氮污染程度升高了3000%。环境的污染对珊瑚系统的破坏是一系列的，比如，[[棘冠海星|棘冠海星]]呈爆发式的密集繁殖。依据2000年的珊瑚样本显示，减少的珊瑚中有66%是这种以珊瑚虫为食的动物造成的。<ref name="cots 1999～2000">{{cite web |url=http://www.reef.crc.org.au/publications/techreport/techrept32.htm |title=CRC REEF RESEARCH CENTRE TECHNICAL REPORT No. 32 — Crown-of-thorns starfish(Acanthaster planci) in the central Great Barrier Reef region. Results of fine-scale surveys conducted in 1999～2000. |accessdate=2007-06-07 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070829092853/http://www.reef.crc.org.au/publications/techreport/techrept32.htm |archivedate=2007-08-29 }}</ref>

有人认为，珊瑚之所以受到了营养物质过剩的影响，背后的原因是海藻导致了光照和氧气竞争的加剧。<ref name=waterquality>{{cite web |author=Great Barrier Reef Marine Park Authority |year=2006 |title=Principal water quality influences on Great Barrier Reef ecosystems |url=http://www.gbrmpa.gov.au/corp_site/key_issues/water_quality/principal_influences.html |accessdate=2006-10-22 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061016155955/http://www.gbrmpa.gov.au/corp_site/key_issues/water_quality/principal_influences.html |archivedate=2006-10-16 }}</ref>除非植食生物出现异常性减少，大堡礁的珊瑚被海藻所替代的情况就不可能出现。<ref>{{cite journal|last=McCook|first=L.J.|date=December 1999|title=Macroalgae, nutrients and phase shifts on coral reefs: scientific issues and management consequences for the Great Barrier Reef|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_coral-reefs_1999-12_18_4/page/357|journal=Coral Reefs|volume=18|issue=4|pages=357–367|doi=10.1007/s003380050213}}</ref>

也有人指出，水质在营养物质过剩的环境下不断恶化，促使了[[传染病|传染病]]在珊瑚间的蔓延。<ref>{{cite web|author=Rachel Nowak|publisher=New Scientist|date=2004-01-11|title=Sewage nutrients fuel coral disease|url=http://www.newscientist.com/article.ns?id=dn4539|accessdate=2006-08-10|archive-date=2006-09-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060910093908/http://www.newscientist.com/article.ns?id=dn4539|dead-url=no}}</ref>大堡礁的珊瑚发病率总体呈较低的水平<ref name="pressure">{{cite web |author=Great Barrier Reef Marine Park Authority |year=2004 |title=Pressure |url=http://www.gbrmpa.gov.au/corp_site/info_services/publications/sotr/latest_updates/corals/part_04.html |accessdate=2007-03-23 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070930184940/http://www.gbrmpa.gov.au/corp_site/info_services/publications/sotr/latest_updates/corals/part_04.html |archivedate=2007-09-30 }}</ref>。Skeletal Eroding Band是一种由[[原生动物|原生动物]]Halofolliculina corallasia引起的疾病，会感染珊瑚群落里6科31种珊瑚。<ref>{{cite web 
